docs.abstract: Mitt Romney’s expected return to politics in a run to be the next senator from Utah has set off a debate over whether he should actively counter President Trump.
docs.snippet: Mitt Romney’s expected return to politics in a run to be the next senator from Utah has set off a debate over whether he should actively counter President Trump.
docs.lead_paragraph: SALT LAKE CITY — A few days after Senator Orrin G. Hatch of Utah announced that he would conclude his tenure after serving 42 years in office, the state’s governor, Gary Herbert, was growing anxious about whether Mitt Romney would run for the seat.

headline.main: ‘I’m Running,’ Romney Says Privately, but as a Trump Friend or Foe?
headline.print_headline: Would Romney Run for Senate As Ally or Foe to the President?

docs.abstract: The Supreme Court ruled that the police were entitled to arrest partygoers in a vacant house and will hear the case of the dusky gopher frog.
docs.snippet: The Supreme Court ruled that the police were entitled to arrest partygoers in a vacant house and will hear the case of the dusky gopher frog.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Supreme Court ruled on Monday that District of Columbia police were entitled to arrest late-night partygoers in a vacant house engaged in what Justice Clarence Thomas called, in announcing the decision from the bench, “utter Bacchanalia.”

headline.main: Supreme Court Considers a Raucous Party and an Endangered Frog
headline.print_headline: Justices Tackle a Docket, Warts and All

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Even as he is embroiled in an immigration policy debate that has focused on whether he used vulgar language to describe Haiti and African countries, President Trump is claiming that he is delivering for black Americans — and that they are repaying him with their support.

docs.abstract: The prospect of more states with less bipartisan representation is likely to increase the intense polarization in Congress.
docs.snippet: The prospect of more states with less bipartisan representation is likely to increase the intense polarization in Congress.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A potential backlash from the new tax law and President Trump’s unpopularity in Democratic-leaning states could combine to turn swaths of blue America even bluer in this year’s elections, a development likely to deepen already intense polarization in Congress.

docs.abstract: In a 6-3 decision, the Supreme Court ruled that a juror’s racist statements required an appeals court to reconsider a death row inmate’s case.
docs.snippet: In a 6-3 decision, the Supreme Court ruled that a juror’s racist statements required an appeals court to reconsider a death row inmate’s case.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Saying that a capital trial in Georgia may have been marred by a juror’s racism, the Supreme Court on Monday gave a death row inmate there a fresh chance to argue that he should receive a new trial.

headline.main: Death Penalty Case Heard by Racist Juror Is Reopened by Supreme Court
headline.print_headline: Racist Juror Leads Court To Reopen Capital Case
